deals.highlightsHtml: Enjoy non-stop fun, food, live entertainment, carnival games, livestock exhibits, demonstrations, shopping, and more at this festive fair
deals.pitchHtml:
• Single-day weekend or weekday general admission (July 25–Aug 12)
  • The fair is open Wednesday-Friday: Noon – Midnight, Saturday-Sunday: 11 a.m. – Midnight
  • View the fairgrounds map.
  • Cash-only on-site parking available each day; free off-site parking with shuttle service available Saturday and Sunday.
  • Outside food and drink allowed if in factory-sealed plastic.
  • No cans, class, hard-sided coolers, outside alcohol allowed, or pets (except service animals). View the full list of prohibited items.

How G-Pass Works: Within an hour of purchase, your G-Pass will be in your account. You must print it out in advance. Discount reflects the merchant’s current ticket prices - price may differ on day of event.

Purchase options:

  • General admission to the OC fair any weekday (Wednesday, Thursday, or Friday)
  • General admission to the OC fair any weekend (Saturday or Sunday)

OC Fair 2018

  • The Food: A vast array of sweet, savory, deep-fried, on-a-stick, in a bowl, and healthy foods, including lasagna nachos from Pignotti’s and Caramel Crack Fries from Biggy’s
  • The Entertainment: Five stages of local and national musicians and performers, including Peking Acrobats—a group of China’s most gifted contortionists, jugglers, and gymnasts—and a Baja Blues series featuring bluegrass legends such as Bill Magee and the Clif Miller Band
  • The Animals: Highlights of the OC Fair include the action of the All-Alaskan racing pigs, the Turkey Stampede, the Oasis Camel Dairy, a petting zoo, and daily livestock exhibits.
  • For the Kids: An Explorium featuring a sand pit, creative corner, rainforest exhibit, and daily performances of The Magic of Frank Thurston
  • Other Festivities: Arts and crafts booths, cooking demonstrations, art galleries and workshops, carnival rides and games, free pop-up selfie museum, and plenty of shopping among local vendors
deals.locationNote: Proceed directly to your entry gate. There is no need to go to the box office. This is your ticket to the event. Contact OC Fair & Event Center at (714) 708-1500 with any questions.

deals.highlightsHtml: Up to 50% off 30+ Los Angeles museums, tours, and attractions, includes Universal Studios, Six Flags & Legoland, Knott’s Berry Farm
deals.pitchHtml:
Choose Between Two Options

  • $170 for a three-day all-inclusive child Go Los Angeles Card
  • $197 for a three-day all-Inclusive adult Go Los Angeles Card

Save up to 50% off combined admission to over 30 top Los Angeles attractions with a 3-Day Go Los Angeles Card All-Inclusive Pass. Pay nothing at the gate. Enjoy the flexibility to choose attractions as you go and do as much as you want each day. The pass includes a free 1-day ticket to Universal Studios, entry to various Hollywood attractions, hop-on / hop-off bus tours, and more. Attractions include:

  • 1-Day Ticket to Universal Studios Hollywood
  • Madame Tussauds Hollywood
  • Warner Bros. Studio Tour Hollywood
  • Pacific Park - Santa Monica Pier
  • Knott's Berry Farm
  • Six Flags Magic Mountain
  • LEGOLAND California
  • Aquarium of the Pacific
  • Rockin Hollywood Tours
  • OUE Skyspace LA
  • And more!

The Deal:

  • See attractions
  • Save up to 55% off vs. purchasing tickets individually. Pay nothing at the gate.
  • Choose attractions as you go from a selection of over 30 Los Angeles attractions, theme parks, museums, tours, cruises, and more.
  • Download your voucher from Groupon within 60 days of purchase. Your pass is activated on your first visit. Use the pass for 3 calendar days within a 14 day period (pass is valid for 2 weeks after activation).

✈ Visiting Los Angeles? Find a spot to rest your head with discounts on LA hotels.

How to redeem (must download Pass before visiting attractions):

  • Access your voucher by visiting your “My vouchers” page or pulling it up in the mobile app.
  • Computer (Recommended): click “Redeem Online” to download your Go City Card pass. Print it out and show your pass at each attraction.
  • Mobile: click “View Voucher” to download your Go City Card pass. Show it right on your phone at each attraction.
  • Purchasing multiple passes? Download each pass before heading to attractions. (Insider tip: if using your smartphone, take a screenshot of each pass in your order with its unique QR code and order number, page 2 of your voucher, for easiest use.)
  • Enjoy!

deals.highlightsHtml: Traditional Korean spa grants guests free reign of four therapy rooms built with detoxifying minerals such as charcoal and Himalayan salt
deals.pitchHtml:
Giving this as a gift? Send it instantly with one of our loving e-cards, or print a handy gift envelope and card.

Spending a day at the spa can rejuvenate weary bodies after a stressful night spent listening to owls’ long-winded lectures. Take a break from hooting with this voucher.

Choose Between Two Options

  • $16.50 for a day-spa visit for one (a $35 value)
  • $31.50 for a day-spa visit for two (a $70 value)

Each day pass grants guests of all ages and genders access to a traditional Korean jimjilbang, complete with four coed mineral-therapy rooms—a salt room, an ice room, a charcoal room, and a yellow-sand room—filled with elements revered for drawing toxins out of the body. Spa-goers can also work up a refreshing sweat inside the saunas attached to the gender-separated locker rooms.
